response.overview: 80 minutes of live performance footage shot on video tape at clubs and galleries in the Los Angeles area from 1977 through 1987. The eight performances range from an early and very raw solo performance by Johanna Went at a small store front club to a pair of performances video taped by Academy Award winning avant garde film director Shirley Clarke. Bonus material includes entertaining and informative audio commentary for each track, recorded by Johanna Went and Mark Wheaton, a slide show of classic live performance photos, and a page of web links accessible when the DVD is played in a computer. CD includes the complete Hyena LP and more.
response.title: Johanna Went: Club Years
